content: I typed in a long email to my provider, and the email failed to send due to "network issues", but there was no way to save the text, so I could not send the email by pasting into an email app without retyping the whole thing. My phone has full network connectivity via WiFi, so this was very disappointing. I also could not send email to support for the same reason and with the same result. This makes the app very unuseful, and I am unlikely to be comfortable attempting to use it for emailing in the future.

Minimal features. The treat me now section does not have as many options as the iOS app. All it has is allergy, UTI & yeast infections. The iOS app has skin conditions as well. I do like being able to make appointments & check prescriptions.
